                <div class="aboutGameSection">
                    <h1>Does it worth your time?</h1>
                    <p class="indent">The combat system is the most time consuming part and you need to accept the fact
                        that dying is
                        part of the game. There is an autosave feature, you cannot manually save and when
                        you die you spawn at the nearest travel point. There is no map, but you get an on-screen marker
                        that guides you to your next objective. Parts of the world are inaccessible until you acquire
                        the relevant power, which means that you will have to revisit many areas in order to collect
                        everything necessary to unlock some of the achievements. But while progressing through the story
                        you unlock shortcuts, which makes navigating your way around the world faster. At the same time,
                        everything you collect will be used for crafting and improving your gear, and that makes
                        exploring worth the time.</p>
                    <h2>First Playthrough</h2>
                    <p class="indent">On your first playthrough you can either play on Normal or Apocalyptic and do not
                        change the
                        difficulty middle-game. You will unlock the majority of the achievements naturally and there are
                        three missable achievements to worry about -
                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[48].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[48].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[48].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>,
                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[38].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[38].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[38].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        and

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[46].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[46].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[46].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>.

                        To save yourself some time from grinding, although they are stackable, pay attention to

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[45].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[45].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[45].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>,
                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[57].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[57].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[57].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        and

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[24].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[24].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[24].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>.

                        While progressing through the story you will eventually get a point-of-no-return warning. At
                        that point make sure you have unlocked

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[14].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[14].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[14].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>,
                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[19].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[19].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[19].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        and

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[21].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[21].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[21].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>.

                        Lastly, if you are playing on Normal, visit The Crucible and unlock

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[27].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[27].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[27].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        and

                        <span class="achievement"> <%= achievements[54].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[54].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text"> <%= achievements[54].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>.

                        I do not recommend playing it on Apocalyptic, since when you die you need to start again from
                        wave 1, and the higher the wave, the higher its difficulty.
                    </p>
                    <h2>Second Playthrough</h2>
                    <p class="indent">The second playthrough should be on NG+ or a.k.a Armageddon mode. If your first
                        playthrough was
                        on Apocalyptic, now you can change it to Normal, if not choose Apocalyptic. This is your
                        clean-up playthrough and you have to defeat the final boss in order to unlock the last available
                        achievements. That means that when you reach the point-of-no-return, make sure that you unlocked
                        everything else.</p>
